title: UMD Women Stay No. 4 in USTFCCCA Poll
text:
UMD Women Stay No. 4 in USTFCCCA Poll 
By Zach Schneider UMD Women Stay No. 4 in USTFCCCA Poll October 7, 2015 Updated Oct 7, 2015 at 1:01 PM CDT 
Duluth, MN (NNCNOW.com) --- The University of Minnesota Duluth (UMD) women's cross country team remains ranked No. 4 in this week's U.S. Track and Field and Cross Country Coaches' Association (USTFCCCA) Division II poll, which was released on Wednesday morning. 
The Bulldogs have won all three events they've raced in 2015, including winning a second straight title this past weekend at the Roy Griak Invitational hosted by the University of Minnesota.
